# Next.js App Router Patterns

## Component Hierarchy

Default to **Server Components**. Only add `'use client'` when truly needed.

```
Page (Server Component)
  └── fetches data directly from Supabase
  └── passes data as props to child components
      └── Interactive parts only → Client Component ('use client')
```

**Use `'use client'` only for:**
- `useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, `useCallback`
- Event handlers (onClick, onChange, onSubmit)
- Browser APIs (localStorage, geolocation)
- TanStack Query hooks (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- Supabase Realtime subscriptions

## Data Fetching in Server Components

```typescript
// app/(dashboard)/customers/page.tsx
import { getAuthContext } from '@/actions/_helpers';
import { createClient } from '@/lib/supabase/server';

export default async function CustomersPage() {
  const supabase = await createClient();
  const { data: customers } = await supabase
    .from('customers')
    .select('*')
    .order('full_name');

  return <CustomerTable customers={customers ?? []} />;
}
```

Never use `fetch()` to call your own API routes from server components — query the DB directly.

## Server Actions

```typescript
'use server';
import { z } from 'zod';
import { getAuthContext } from '@/actions/_helpers';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';

const schema = z.object({
  full_name: z.string().min(1).max(100),
  phone: z.string().min(8),
});

type ActionResult<T = void> =
  | { success: true; data: T }
  | { success: false; error: string };

export async function createCustomerAction(input: unknown): Promise<ActionResult> {
  const parsed = schema.safeParse(input);
  if (!parsed.success) return { success: false, error: 'Invalid input' };

  try {
    const { supabase, tenantId } = await getAuthContext();
    const { error } = await supabase
      .from('customers')
      .insert({ ...parsed.data, tenant_id: tenantId });

    if (error) throw error;
    revalidatePath('/customers');
    return { success: true, data: undefined };
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('[createCustomerAction]', error);
    return { success: false, error: 'Failed to create customer' };
  }
}
```

## Form Handling with Server Actions

```typescript
'use client';
import { useTransition } from 'react';
import { createCustomerAction } from '@/actions/customers';

export function CreateCustomerForm() {
  const [isPending, startTransition] = useTransition();

  function handleSubmit(e: React.FormEvent<HTMLFormElement>) {
    e.preventDefault();
    const formData = new FormData(e.currentTarget);
    startTransition(async () => {
      const result = await createCustomerAction(Object.fromEntries(formData));
      if (!result.success) toast.error(result.error);
    });
  }

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
      {/* form fields */}
      <button type="submit" disabled={isPending}>
        {isPending ? 'Creating...' : 'Create Customer'}
      </button>
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Routing Conventions

```
app/
  layout.tsx                    — Root layout (fonts, providers)
  page.tsx                      — Marketing home page
  (dashboard)/                  — Route group (no URL segment)
    layout.tsx                  — Auth gate + TenantProvider + AppShell
    dashboard/page.tsx          — /dashboard
    customers/
      page.tsx                  — /customers (list)
      [id]/page.tsx             — /customers/[id] (detail)
  api/
    webhooks/stripe/route.ts    — POST /api/webhooks/stripe
    queue-board/route.ts        — GET /api/queue-board
```

Route groups `(name)` are used for shared layouts without affecting the URL.

## Middleware

Middleware runs on every request. Keep it fast:
- Refresh Supabase session (required by Supabase SSR)
- Check auth state from cookie/JWT — **avoid DB queries when possible**
- Redirect unauthenticated users on dashboard routes

```typescript
// middleware.ts — keep this lean
export const config = {
  matcher: ['/((?!_next/static|_next/image|favicon.ico|.*\\.(?:svg|png|jpg|jpeg|gif|webp)$).*)'],
};
```

## Loading and Error States

```typescript
// app/(dashboard)/customers/loading.tsx
export default function Loading() {
  return <CustomerTableSkeleton />;
}

// app/(dashboard)/customers/error.tsx
'use client';
export default function Error({ error, reset }: { error: Error; reset: () => void }) {
  return (
    <div>
      <p>Failed to load customers</p>
      <button onClick={reset}>Try again</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## TanStack Query (Client-Side Only)

Use for data that needs real-time updates, optimistic updates, or polling:

```typescript
'use client';
import { useQuery, useMutation, useQueryClient } from '@tanstack/react-query';

export function QueueDisplay({ branchId }: { branchId: string }) {
  const { data: queue } = useQuery({
    queryKey: ['queue', branchId],
    queryFn: async () => {
      const res = await fetch(`/api/queue-board?branch=${branchId}`);
      return res.json();
    },
  });
}
```

Prefer Supabase Realtime over polling for queue data.

## Environment Variables

```typescript
// Access env vars — always through the typed env helper
import { env } from '@/lib/env';
const url = env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL;

// Never access process.env directly — bypasses validation
const url = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL; // avoid
```

## Image Optimization

Always use `next/image` for images:
```typescript
import Image from 'next/image';
<Image src={shop.logo_url} alt={shop.name} width={80} height={80} />
```

Never use `<img>` tags for content images.
